The paper deals with inconsistency in pairwise comparisons, which is a topic related to decision making and optimization. The use of mathematical methods to construct rankings suggests a connection to data mining (cs.DM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The introduction of new concepts such as generalized tournaments and double tournaments suggests a connection to graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the relationship between the most inconsistent set of pairwise comparisons with ties and the set cover problem suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC).
